public interface SequenceReader
extends java.io.Closeable

Interface for reading data from a stream in key/value form.

hasNext

boolean hasNext()
                throws java.io.IOException
Return true if there is a next item. Initially the reader is positioned on the first item so that hasNext() returns true and you can then call key() and value()
